OL,3,CInspectors highlight overcrowding,
OL,4,Cdrugs and rise in self-harm at prison
OL,6,FAfter identifying a rise in the use of
OL,7,Fdrugs during a previous inspection,
OL,8,Fthe report said it still remained a
OL,9,F"significant concern", with the
OL,10,Fproportion of positive mandatory drugs
OL,11,Ftests increasing from 25% to 28%.
OL,13,FBut it did say leaders were using
OL,14,Fintelligence to good effect to bring
OL,15,Fdrugs rates down, such as suspicion
OL,16,Ftesting and intelligence-led cell
OL,17,Fsearching.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/6
